<HTML><title>Perspectives</title>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<h2><center><I><B>Individuals Who Save Get Third-Class 
Treatment Under The Ordinary Income Tax</h2></center></B></I>
<hr>
<P>
Our government rather freely provides loans to many foreign governments,
some of whom are (or were) communist, socialist, big government
central planners, dictators, or scoundrels.  Not infrequently,
these loans carry a zero rate of interest or a rate that's far
below market.  No collateral is required.
<P>
Many, if not most, of these loans are eventually written off as
defaults, severely written down, or rolled over with little prospect
for repayment.  In aggregate, these loans (and gifts or subsidies)
from our taxpayers' pockets amount to mega-billions of dollars
every year.
<P>
Contrast these loans, gifts, or subsidies to foreigners with the
refusal of our government to properly consider its own taxpayers'
IRA assets as representing private saving that will enhance the
government's tax revenues, not reduce them!
<P>
Rather than considering IRAs as an asset, the government treats
IRA tax deferrals as wasted spending; not unlike the writing off
of a governmental loan to, or subsidized trade with, Iraq, or
some socialist/communist country.
<P>
Completely ignored by the government are the facts that IRA assets:
 (a) are held in trust (by law) for the future payment of taxes;
(b) are invested in income-producing assets (not some foreign
government's and bureaucracy's boondoggle); (c) provide growing
amounts of capital for business enterprises and other productive
private uses, including jobs; (d) create ever-growing gains that
contribute to the economic growth of our nation; and (e) provide
tax revenue gains for our government.
<P>
It's amazing and most distressing to recognize how our government
freely gives away taxpayer money to foreigners (and then cavalierly
writes it off), while denying its taxpayers the eminently sound
financial structure of universal, unlimited, tax-deductible IRAs,
so that all taxpayers will save more to produce more!  Taxing
saving &quot;twice&quot; or more is bad enough, but then giving
away those diminished tax receipts to fund foreign boondoggles
equals third-class or &quot;steerage&quot; treatment for U.S.
taxpayers who save and invest!
<P>
<I>It's time for all savers and investors to stand up and fight
for tax sanity and their financial well-being.</I>
<p>
[<a href="/savers/">Home</a>][<a href="../library.html">Library</a>]
</BODY>

</HTML>
