<center>
<h2><i>Welcome to Town Hall's Policy Roundtable</h2></i></center>
<br><br>
Have you ever wanted to meet with the people who build the intellectual foundations on which public policy is made? Now everyone can. The Policy Roundtable is your chance to rub elbows with leading conservative thinkers and activists. <p>
Each Monday we will introduce you to that week's experts.  Follow the links below to go to the appropriate topic.  There you will find a brief introduction and an opening statement.  Once you're finished reading you can submit your questions and comments by selecting "reply".  Our experts will check in often to field your questions and discuss your comments. <p>

<ul>
<i>Start Date --  </i> <i> Topic </i> <br>
<li>March 19 -- 
<a href="http://www.townhall.com/townhall/wgw-forum/ac/dispatch.cgi/policy_roundtable/browse/thread/d/decreasing/d/0/100001">Immigration</a>, with the Heritage Foundation's Joe Cobb and Americans for Tax Reform's Scott Hoffman.<br>
<li>March 25 --  <a href="http://www.townhall.com/townhall/wgw-forum/ac/dispatch.cgi/policy_roundtable/browse/thread/d/decreasing/d/0/100050">Encryption</a>, with Jim Lucier of Americans for Tax Reform, Adam Thierer of the Heritage Foundation, and Michael Vlahos of the Progress & Freedom Foundation.<br>
</ul><p><br>
<center>
<hr size ="4" width="40%"></center>
<br><br>
<center>
<h4>To get the most from the Policy Roundtable you should keep the following in mind:</h4></center> 
<ul>
<li>Anyone may read the public discussions.  To post a message, you will need to <a href="/townhall/wgw-forum/ac/dispatch.cgi/_user/addForm/short">register</a>. If you have already registered for Town Hall's new Town Meeting software, you can skip this step.<p>
<li>To change your password, log in and select your name from the <a href="/townhall/wgw-forum/ac/dispatch.cgi/_user">registered users</a> list.  Choose the "modify" button that appears on the linked page.   <p> 
<li>Using the procedure listed above, you can modify how the forum looks and acts.<p> 
<li><b>Important Note:</b> Unfortunately, registered users of Town Hall's old Town Meetings will need to <a href="/townhall/wgw-forum/ac/dispatch.
cgi/_user/addForm/short">re-register</a> to use this application.  Fortunately, doing so is easy and quick. 
</ul>
Please note, your use of these areas implies your acceptance of the <a href="http://www.townhall.com/townhall/wgw-forum/ac/conduct.html">the rules of conduct</a> that govern their use.
Please send any comments to <a href="mailto:jjohnson@townhall.com">Jeff Johnson</a>.
